  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This synthetic package carries a W-CON-01 weakness: the decision record records outcome Accepted while several CredibilityFactor entries omit both requiredLevel and achievedLevel, leaving the acceptance decision without grounding in structured factor evidence.",
